                     <p>
                        <seg type="docType">Covenant.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_111716">Bramley (Hampshire)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_116029">Sherborne St John (Hampshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1667">19 Chas. II. June 1, 1667</origDate>. Indenture made between (1) John Thorner of Kings Cleere, Hampshire, and
                        Jane his wife; (2) Sir William Gardiner of London, baronet and Dame Jane his
                        wife; (3) Francis Gregg of St. Clement Danes, Middlesex, gent., Abraham
                        Downing of St. Clement Danes, Middlesex, serjeant skinner to the King and
                        Thomas Willoughby of Kings Cleere, Hampshire, gent., being a covenant by (1)
                        and (2) to (3) concerning lands in Bramley, Hampshire; Sherborne St John,
                        Hampshire; (signed and sealed by John Thorner; Jane Thorner; Sir William
                        Gardiner; Jane Gardiner; Francis Gregg; Abraham Downing; and also presumably
                        sealed by Thomas Willoughby).</p>
                  </msItem>
